	<text>
		<body>
			<pb n="1R"/>
				<p rend="align(right)"><placeName>Louisville Ky</placeName>&#44; <date>May 8th 1854</date></p>
				<p><addressee>Revd Isaac Leeser</addressee>&#44; Editor of the Occident</p>
			<p rend="indent(2)">Dear Sir</p>
			<p rend="indent(3)">Herewith you will receive advertisement&#44;<lb/> which please insert in your periodical once&#44; &#47;provided it will ap<lb/>pear in your <date>June</date> number&#58;&#47;&#44; and forward account to me for ad<lb/> justment.  Should any <sic>enquiry</sic> be made of you&#44; I am authorized to say<lb/> that the salary will be the least about 600 Dollars p. a. and<lb/> that a good practical English Scholar only can obtain the<lb/> situation.</p>
			<p rend="indent(6)">Respectfully yours</p>
			<p rend="indent(5)">By order of the Directory</p>
			<p rend="indent(8)"><persName role="author">B H. Gotthelf</persName> Secretary</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">Teacher wanted.</p>
				<p>The congregational School about to be established in K. K. Adas Israel in <placeName>Louisville Ky</placeName> is desirous of procuring the services<lb/> of a practical English Scholar capable of imparting instruction<lb/> in the Hebrew language and Religion.  A liberal salary<lb/> will be given and Testimonials of character and qualifications<lb/> required.  To <add>&#63;</add> further particulars address</p>
			<p rend="indent(3)"><persName>H. Uberdorfer</persName> Pres.of the Board of <lb/>Directors</p>
			<p rend="indent(3)">or <persName role="author">Revd. B. H. Gotthelf</persName> Sec.</p>
				<p>P. S. I will communicate to you in a few day&#39;<sic>s</sic> my success <del>of a</del><lb/> in distributing your bibles&#8212;and other particulars concerning the<lb/> congregational affairs&#59; which are very encouraging.  I have</p>
				<p rend="The following is written at the bottom of the page.">&#35;</p>
			<pb n="1V"/>
				<p>sold 19 copies&#44; but as yet not received one single Dollar<lb/> for it.&#8212; I Hope you will <sic>safe</sic> a little space for me<lb/> in your next Occident.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">Send the Occident for <date>April</date> &#38; <date>May</date> To</p>
			<p rend="indent(2)"><persName>Marcus Straus</persName> in <placeName><sic>Lesxington</sic> Ky</placeName>&#44; and continue<lb/> to send the same regularly.  If you prefer it&#44; you<lb/> may address them to me&#44; and <hi rend="underline">I</hi> will send them&#44; as<lb/> it may be perhaps<del>s</del> the safest way.&#8212;</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">To <sic>morrow</sic> evening will be a congreg. meeting&#44; the result<lb/> of which will be the principal<del>e</del> tendency of my <add>next</add> communi<lb/>cation.</p>
				<p rend="Note&#58;">Scribbled line next to &#8220;congreg&#8221; in the text above.</p>
			<p rend="indent(8)">Truly &#38; most respectfully yours&#8212;</p>
			<p rend="indent(8)"><persName role="author">B H Gotthelf</persName>.</p>
				<p>&#8212;&#8212;&#8212;&#8212;</p>
				<p>Should you know of any good Teacher&#44; such as we want&#44;<lb/> I wish you would let me know privately&#8212; For a good<lb/> Teacher the situation would soon become a permanent one<lb/> and the congregation would willingly pay seven or eight<lb/> Hundred Dollars after the first year.&#8212;Answer as soon<lb/> as convenient.&#8212;</p>
				<p rend="The following is written at the bottom left.">20&#45;238</p>
				<p rend=" The following is written at the bottom center.">&#35;001<lb/>6&#45;694</p>
				<p rend="The following is written at the bottom right.">&#47;348N6V&#44;<lb/>Judaica&#44;<lb/>V&#45;early Ky</p>
